Throughout this paper, the notation $\mathbb{N}$ stands for the set of all the positive integers; all measure spaces are assumed to be $\sigma$-finite; all C*-algebras are assumed to be separable; and all representations of C*-algebras are assumed to be on separable infinite-dimensional Hilbert spaces.

