The following is the Cuntz-Krieger uniqueness theorem for ultragraph C*-algebras.

\begin{teorema}[{\cite[Theorem~6.7]{Tomforde:JOT03}}]\label{Cuntz-Krieger uni thm for ultragraph alg}
Let $\mathcal{G}$ be an ultragraph which satisfies Condition~(L). Then for a Cuntz-Krieger $\mathcal{G}$-family $\{P_A,S_e:A\in \mathcal{G}^0, e\in \mathcal{G}^1\}$ in a C*-algebra $B$ satisfying $P_A\neq 0$ whenever $A \neq \emptyset$, the ultragraph C*-algebra $C^*(\mathcal{G})$ is isomorphic with $C^*(P_A,S_e)$ via the map $p_A \mapsto P_A, s_e \mapsto S_e$.
