Then the set $B_A$ is well-defined. Furthermore, $B_A$ is an orthonormal basis of $H_A$ and, for $A,C\in \mathcal{G}^0$, we have that $B_A\cap B_C=B_{A\cap C}$ and $B_A\cup B_C=B_{A\cup C}$.
\end{lema}

